Committed to closing the gap

Ericsson Television 
Ltd. is wholly 
committed to 
closing the gap in 
gender pay in the 
UK and we realise
there is a great 
deal more work to 
be done to bridge 
the gap in our 
business. 

Ericsson Internal  |  2018-02-21

We are currently working in partnership with the Engineering 
Development Trust, promoting STEM in schools, colleges, and 
universities with the aim to encourage young girls into engineering 
at an early age.
On January 31, 2018, Ericsson partnered with One Equity Partners.  
As such, Ericsson Media Solutions, which is currently part of 
Ericsson. will become a part of a separate global company. 
Ericsson Television Ltd. will be included under the new terms.
As part of this transition, Ericsson Television Ltd. will work to place 
a significant focus on attracting and retaining females into the 
business.

Moving towards the future

Moving forward,  we will be reviewing our internal policies and practices for 
recruitment and internal career opportunities to support and help address the 
gender pay gap. Our ambition is to have a much better gender-balanced 
workforce at all levels in the organisation. 

Heather Andrade- Neumann
Head of Human Resources
Ericsson Media Solutions

Angel Ruiz
President and CEO
Ericsson Media Solutions

